t up  |strong="935" srcloc="WLC:JON.2.7.7" \w* \w  to You ,  |strong="413" srcloc="WLC:JON.2.7.8" \w* \w  to  |strong="413" srcloc="WLC:JON.2.7.10" \w* \w  Your holy  |strong="6944" srcloc="WLC:JON.2.7.12" \w* \w  temple .  |strong="1964" srcloc="WLC:JON.2.7.11" \w* \v 8 \w  Those who cling to  |strong="8104" srcloc="WLC:JON.2.8.1" \w* \w  worthless  |strong="7723" srcloc="WLC:JON.2.8.3" \w* \w  idols  |strong="1892" srcloc="WLC:JON.2.8.2" \w* \w  forsake  |strong="5800" srcloc="WLC:JON.2.8.5" \w* \w  [His] loving devotion .  |strong="2617" srcloc="WLC:JON.2.8.4" \w* \f + \fr 2.8 \ft Forms of the Hebrew "chesed" are translated here and in most cases throughout the Scriptures as "loving devotion"; the range of meaning includes "love", "goodness", "kindness", "faithfulness", and "mercy", as well as "loyalty to a covenant". \f* \v 9 \w  But I ,  |strong="589" srcloc="WLC:JON.2.9.1" \w* \w  with the voice  |strong="6963" srcloc="WLC:JON.2.9.2" \w* \w  of thanksgiving ,  |strong="8426" srcloc="WLC:JON.2.9.3" \w* \w  will sacrifice  |strong="2076" srcloc="WLC:JON.2.9.4" \w* \w  to You .  |srcloc="WLC:JON.2.9.5" \w* \w  I will fulfill  |strong="7999" srcloc="WLC:JON.2.9.8" \w* \w  what  |strong="834" srcloc="WLC:JON.2.9.6" \w* \w  I have vowed .  |strong="5087" srcloc="WLC:JON.2.9.7" \w* \w  Salvation  |strong="3444" srcloc="WLC:JON.2.9.9" \w* \w  is from the LORD ! ”  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:JON.2.9.10" \w* \v 10 \w  And the LORD  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:JON.2.10.2" \w* \w  commanded  |strong="559" srcloc="WLC:JON.2.10.1" \w* \w  the fish ,  |strong="1709" srcloc="WLC:JON.2.10.3" \w* \w  and it vomited  |strong="6958" srcloc="WLC:JON.2.10.4" \w* \w  Jonah  |strong="3124" srcloc="WLC:JON.2.10.6" \w* \w  onto  |strong="413" srcloc="WLC:JON.2.10.7" \w* \w  dry land .  |strong="3004" srcloc="WLC:JON.2.10.8" \w* 
